{"total_count": 8, "incomplete_results": false, "items": [{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/13", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/13/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/13/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/13/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/13", "id": 627098374, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU2MjcwOTgzNzQ=", "number": 13, "title": "Entrypoint collides with other pytest plugins", "user": {"login": "desolat", "id": 188917, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4ODkxNw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/188917?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat", "html_url": "https://github.com/desolat", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/desolat/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2020-05-29T08:33:20Z", "updated_at": "2020-06-05T11:27:35Z", "closed_at": "2020-06-02T06:49:42Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The pytest `entry_point` used for pytest-dotenv is named \"env\" and thus does collide with other pytest plugins e.g. [pytest-env](https://github.com/MobileDynasty/pytest-env). Thus only one of these plugins can be installed and used. \r\n\r\nI'd suggest using the specific plugin name \"dotenv\" for the pytest `entry_point`. This is also suggested in the [pytest documentation](https://docs.pytest.org/en/latest/writing_plugins.html#making-your-plugin-installable-by-others).", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/12", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/12/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/12/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/12/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/12", "id": 589368728, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1ODkzNjg3Mjg=", "number": 12, "title": "Add ability to pass as argument", "user": {"login": "Amertz08", "id": 8210235, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjgyMTAyMzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/8210235?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08", "html_url": "https://github.com/Amertz08", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Amertz08/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2020-03-27T19:28:57Z", "updated_at": "2020-06-05T14:05:41Z", "closed_at": "2020-06-05T11:26:56Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "It would be nice to be able to pass `--env-file` or something similar as a CLI option. I switch stuff like databases off `.env` files and would like to avoid maintaining a 1-to-1 of `pytest.ini` files and `.env` files. Avoids `pytest-dev.ini -> dev.env`, `pytest-qa.ini -> qa.env` and `pytest-prod.ini -> prod.env`.\r\n", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/11", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/11/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/11/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/11/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/11", "id": 551333586, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1NTEzMzM1ODY=", "number": 11, "title": "Environment variables are not found when pytest is started in shell", "user": {"login": "lgrosser-tiplu", "id": 51316240, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUxMzE2MjQw", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/51316240?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu", "html_url": "https://github.com/lgrosser-tiplu", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/lgrosser-tiplu/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2020-01-17T10:30:43Z", "updated_at": "2020-04-16T20:48:34Z", "closed_at": "2020-01-17T10:40:49Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hi,\r\nI am using Pycharm 2019.3.1, the package works great when I start pytest by using right-click on the respective test folder from within Pycharm, all environment variables are found and used. However, if I start pytest from the console, the variables are not found. Am I missing a cli parameter that tells pytest to use pytest-dotenv?", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/10", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/10/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/10/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/10/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/10", "id": 518409613, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1MTg0MDk2MTM=", "number": 10, "title": "How to get PyCharm test run working with pytest-dotenv?", "user": {"login": "namgivu", "id": 1185192, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExODUxOTI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1185192?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu", "html_url": "https://github.com/namgivu", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/namgivu/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2019-11-06T11:23:23Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-07T09:28:59Z", "closed_at": "2019-11-07T09:28:24Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I succeeded with [running my test with pytest-dotenv](https://github.com/namgivu/pytest-start/commit/1fc0e1acc3b375da0089d2f41b6fa47801690f8a) from command line as below quote\r\n```\r\n============================= test session starts ==============================\r\nplatform linux -- Python 3.6.9, pytest-5.2.2, py-1.8.0, pluggy-0.13.0\r\nrootdir: /my/local/path/to/pytest-start, inifile: pytest.ini\r\nplugins: forked-1.1.3, dotenv-0.4.0, xdist-1.30.0\r\ncollected 1 item\r\n\r\ntests/test_dotenv.py .\r\n\r\n============================== 1 passed in 0.01s ===============================\r\n```\r\n\r\nThough when running the test with PyCharm test run mode, the plugin not working. \r\nSo my question is how to get PyCharm test run working with pytest-dotenv?", "performed_via_github_app": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/8", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/8/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pytest-dotenv/issues/8/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/quiqua/pyte